<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-12T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-12T06:00:00-05:00" n="177" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.01 M 31/215: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-12T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 12,
                                        1925—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received June 12—8:23
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>172. Your 133, April 25, 5 p.m. I am informally advised by the Foreign
                            Office that so far as it is aware there are no existing treaty
                            engagements towards third parties affecting the territories in question
                            and that the proviso was inserted merely as a precaution of a general
                            nature.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Houghton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>